caption: One of my favorite meals in new orleans! We had city greens cater the morning of the wedding and they did not disappoint! Being vegan in new orleans is hard but city greens made it delicious and for the first time all trip I felt full (hello real protein) Plus they made my favorite cup of sweet tea all trip. All the non vegans also loved their chicken wraps and not a single wrap was leftover for the groom that night

Thought it was great there was finally a healthy option at NOLA airport. 3 times I’ve been disappointed. One time they had two people there but neither could checkout that cash register and said I needed to come back in 30 min. Today there was a line, 2 people working, only 1 was making the food and she kept pulling her phone out and texting IN FRONT OF EVERYONE! She also kept ducking to the back (I can only imagine to continue texting on her phone). Waited in line (with only 5 people ahead of me) for 30 min before I had to leave because my flight was boarding. Don’t bother if you’re flight boards within 30 min because you won’t get your food. Such a disappointment.
Pretty healthy-Ish food at a decent price for downtown fare.
Great atmosphere if a little hard to find at first. The selection of ingredients is awesome, and the pricing for what you get is pretty fantastic when you factor in overhead
There Chicken Wraps And Shrimp Pasta Salads Are So Gooood

I don’t know what the food taste like because I never got that far. I went to the City Greens in the New Orleans airport (12/27/19 at about 8:30pm). A lady with braids took my order. During the process of making my salad she had to push her hair out of her face and away from the food about 5 times. I tolerated it because she was placing the food in a bowl with utensils. However, when she got to the chicken she had to use her fingers to keep the chicken from falling out of the scooper. I tolerated that as well, but then she got to the eggs and had to use her entire gloved hands. I told her “I cannot eat your salad because your hands were in your hair and then your hands were touching all over my food.” She proceeded to throw the food away. I think everyone knows those handling food need to have their hair tied behind them and some managers go the extra mile and require head wraps. I am hoping something will be done about this. I could not find any contact information for the manager on-line to make a direct complaint.

There is a 50/50 chance they will get your order correct and another 50/50 chance someone will actually answer the phone to find out they sent you the wrong order. Think you can call corporate?  Think again.  What happened, City Greens?  You were once my #1.  Now, I'm done;  I want a divorce.  Next!

I got a tuna salad here that had two, small strips of tuna in it for a whole big bowl of greens. And the dressing wasn’t good. Then I got a turkey wrap that tasted pretty good but had about three small pieces of turkey in it for a huge wrap. Are the owners of this place broke and trying to stay afloat, or is this just a good old fashioned rip off? I do not recommend this place. To the restaurant- why are you so stingy with the protein? Its horribly tacky and ruins your otherwise tasty food.
Love the southwestern salad!
Good. Light cuisine and tasty.
The food here is healthy (if you want it to be) and fresh and the line moves quickly even during the lunch rush.

Originally had a salad from here when I came to interview at the time I was questioning what is all the hoopla. However, now that I’m here, I went back and got another one. Delicious 🤤. There just a right amount of dressing added so you have the full flavor of the veggies and chicken. 👍🏽 will return
This was a great non fried option. I frequent a place back home like this called Chopt.
Decent salad but kind of overpriced. Got it delivered but did get a fork or napkins...would have been nice to get a fork with my salad 🙄
Always get a delicious meal at City Greens
Great place to go for a healthy, tasty salad with options in the CBD.
Lots of healthy, good tasting options.

Great service, fresh enough, but a bit pricey if you're not careful.  Ordered a build your own and the price is $8.95 with no meats and only four standard toppings. I added avocado and brussel sprouts for $2.00 ea. and went over the four count by four. The standard options I paid for were things like carrots and cucumbers and red onions. This crazy overage cost me an extra four bucks. My salad ended up costing me $18.95 with tip included. Ouch!!!
Good salads!
Healthy food that tastes good. On the pricey side.
Spent $15 dollars on a small salad. Way over priced for what you get ,never will I go there again!
Pretty pricey for what it is. Salads are quick but they aren't anything to write home about. Friendly staff too. Good for a quick bite which is what I do with it.
(Translated by Google) Healthy lunch. Fresh products  (Original) Pranzo salutare. Prodotti freschi

I only ate here once. The food was expensive and flavorless. Nothing fresh! I must have been the first customer of the day,  because a bunch of employees were standing around looking like they weren't sure what they should be doing. I saw no menu,  and was not offered one. I was greeted at the door by a friendly employee,  but not offered any advice as to where to find a menu. They all just looked at me like I was an alien. Except for the cashier. She didn't want to be there. She was pretty rude. I got what looked like a promising little bowl of pasta out of a refrigerated case. It was bland, overcooked,  soggy and quite disgusting. For a place called "City Greens" one would think you could find something decent and fresh.
Great!
great salads, super fresh! easy to customize. great staff! love this place!
Very good food, healthy and delicious.
Great gf options, and very light after all the other heavy foods we have had this week.
Love it!
Awesome!
Salads are ok but need to try their organic juices.
salads are fine,  but they are overpriced for what you get.  I would much prefer to go to Welty's 3 blocks away where you can get double the salad (with higher quality) for an extra dollar or two.

This is great healthy option for a quick lunch. Good food at reasonable prices, good value. Professional, efficient, courteous service. Earth-friendly packaging. Tasty, creative salads. Very cool that they grow their own produce.  Good for you, good for the planet. If I lived here I would be a regular.
Delicious and fresh, it doesn't get much better than this. Eat like this during the week and the weekend indulgences are easier to maintain.
Really nice wrap. The soup was a little disappointing
Fantastic!  I am a big fan of fresh salads and this place has awesome ingedients and is quick.  The employees are efficient and keep you moving through the line.
Delicious salad and nice clean location. You can build your own salad or wrap or order from premade options. Very fresh food.
The seared tuna on the chopped Cobb was excellent! Great price!

Really friendly and helpful girl at Elmwood location. And patient, we’d never been here and had a million questions. The ingredients we could see her putting on were fresh and real, not fake gunk.  We loved both soups! I forget the name of each one but I’m picky and they were both quality ingredients and delicious. She added cheese on top if we wanted- real cheese, and offered a small side of fresh sourdough bread that was so good! The wrap was huge and really good. I went back the same afternoon for a cup of the soup to take home. The price was reasonable. There was a counter with water and cups available and lemon wedges. The water tasted filtered. Very clean place too.
Good salad. A little pricey, but service is good.
Superduper expensive salads

Wonderful options. Tasty food. Fresh, nutritious and filling! I do wish they gave out little paper lists to the customers to fill out for the build-your-own options. The choices are so numerous that it is difficult to make up your mind on the spot
Food is healthy but tastes ok........
If you are looking for a fast and healthy option, City Greens is the place. You can build your custom salad or pick one of their delicious options on the menu. Their press juices are just as good.
Quick and good

One of the few healthy options downtown. Always pretty tasty but perhaps slow down and put just slightly more care into the preparation of each salad.

Always good for a delicious lunch salad or wrap. Get her before 11:30 am to avoid the lunchtime rush, which can get long!! Really efficient servers and outdoor seating make this a great spot for social lunches or a salad to go

Would be five stars if it weren't so expensive. Otherwise great service and salads.
Friendly staff amazing fresh food

TERRIBLE customer service experience. Quality of the food does not make up for it. I called a pick-up order for a meeting. Not only were they late, there were a few items missing in my order. I called to complain because it is something that has happened before. They were supposed to deliver the missing items but after two hours I had to call again because they never did. Finally, after two and a half hours they brought the items missing from the original order. HOWEVER, there was still one item missing!! Just unbelievable. I didn't waste my time calling again and just wrote a review instead. Think twice before ordering specially for business events.
I absolutely love this place. The wraps are delicious and very very filling. I can only eat half. No guilt heading here for lunch on occasion😘
Great selection.  Perfect quick delicious lunch spot.
This needs to be a franchise!

My experience in the past has been good at city greens. The food is always delicious. This past time, however, I ordered the chopped salad and they were out of avocado. When they asked if I want something else to replace it I asked if I could replace it with chicken. They said that is a premium meat so I still got charged the full price of the salad plus the premium meat. I thought that was a bit petty.
Best wrap I have ever had in my life.
Ate here while visiting NOLA . Our whole group loved it and all wished we had one at home. Delicious, fresh, salads and wraps. Highly recommend.
Loved it!!! needs more locations but I'm sure they're working on it.

I saved for months to vacation in New Orleans for my 25th birthday. As a vegetarian, I chose this place for lunch and spent the entire night projectile vomiting my overpriced spinach tofu wrap. Thanks for ruining my birthday AND tofu wraps. Next time I visit this city, I'd rather lick powdered sugar from the street than eat here.
Fresh, delicious, great experience with delivery!

Good spot for a healthy lunch in the CBD. The BBQ chicken wrap is excellent.  Tip: To avoid a wait, place your order online and show up 10 minutes after it is supposed to be ready. They get extremely busy during lunch.

My office mates and I have ordered from City Greens 3 times in the last 2 weeks.  On the first attempt they delivered my order to someone else, so it was over an hour before we got our food, which were two Filet & Mango salads that did not turn out to be as good as they sounded on the menu.  On the second order we got several build-your-owns, one of which was delivered with the wrong greens and took about 45 minutes to arrive (only about 5 minutes longer than the longest of the quoted delivery time range).  So today we ordered a third time, expecting the long delivery time, and this time a salad which had been ordered with no onions and sub baby spinach for the romaine arrived full of onions and with kale instead of baby spinach (with no onions written on top of the clear container).  At least 3 of us order salads for lunch every singe weekday, looking at the menu we thought this would be a great new place in addition to Terrazu which we order from the majority of the time.  After our experiences with City Greens I believe getting a better variety is not worth the chance that we won't be getting what we ordered and we'll be getting it in an hour versus the 20-30 minutes Terrazu usually manages to deliver within.  The quality of the food is good, but it doesn't make up for the service mistakes.  Additionally, they are one of the few (if not only) restaurant we've ordered from in CBD that charges a delivery fee.
Great place! I had the seared tuna avocado salad and it was phenomenal! Service was good too, everyone was friendly. I love the "big-city" vibe I felt inside the restaurant.

This place recently opened in the CBD. A friend told me about it. Absolutely delicious made to order fresh salads and wraps. It's a popular and convenient lunch only spot. The food is fresh, diverse & organic. I had the salad of the day which was vegan-- yum. I so glad this place opened and glad greens are popular in the city. I will definitely be back!
